I have an ML Dashboard project using FastAPI backend and HTML/JS frontend. Currently, graphs are generated using matplotlib and sent as base64 images.

I want to UPGRADE the visualization layer to interactive charts using Chart.js WITHOUT changing my ML logic, pipeline, or model outputs.


🎯 Objective
Replace static matplotlib graphs with interactive Chart.js graphs
Keep backend ML logic unchanged
Only modify how graph data is returned and rendered

🚨 STRICT RULES
DO NOT change model training or evaluation logic
DO NOT change preprocessing or pipelines
DO NOT change metrics calculation
ONLY replace visualization layer

🔧 BACKEND CHANGES
Instead of returning base64 images, return structured JSON for graphs:
Example:

{
"roc_curve": {
"fpr": [...],
"tpr": [...],
"auc": 0.995
}
}

Do this for:
Confusion Matrix → matrix values
ROC Curve → fpr, tpr, auc
PR Curve → precision, recall
Residual Plot → y_pred, residuals
Actual vs Predicted → y_true, y_pred
Learning Curve → train_sizes, train_scores, val_scores

🎨 FRONTEND CHANGES
Use Chart.js (CDN):
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>

Replace graphs with elements
Create reusable JS functions to render charts

🎨 DESIGN REQUIREMENTS
Use theme colors:

Primary: #667eea
Accent: #f5576c
Success: #00f2fe
Charts must include:

Smooth lines
Tooltips
Legends
Responsive layout

📦 OUTPUT REQUIRED
Updated backend response format (JSON graphs)
Frontend JS functions for Chart.js
Canvas-based rendering replacing images
No breaking changes to existing APIs

⚠️ IMPORTANT
This is a visualization upgrade only.

Preserve all existing ML functionality.